1. Which of these are differences between the B2B and D2C markets?
Ans: D. A and B

A. D2C commerce merchants provide incredible shopping experiences, while B2B commerce involves a multitude of complex relationships and the movement of bulk goods.
B. B2B purchases often require negotiated, account-specific pricing and terms, while D2C commerce uses price books with discounts via promotions.

2. True or false: While many D2C customers choose to remain anonymous, registration gives companies a lot more insight into who their customers are and what they need.
Ans: A. True
